Bring a #large pot{} of salted water to a boil with the @brown rice{3/4%cup} and
@veggie stock concentrate{1}. Cook, as you would pasta, for ~{25-30%minutes},
or until tender. Drain, return to the #pot, and cover to steam.

Cut the @Chinese eggplant{1} into ½-inch cubes. Thinly slice the
@yellow squash{1} into rounds. Thinly slice the @scallions{2} on a diagonal,
keeping the greens and whites separate. Thinly slice the @garlic{2%cloves}.
Cut the @lime{1} into wedges.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over
medium heat. Add the eggplant and squash and cook, tossing, ~{7-8%minutes}
or until tender. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Set aside.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in the same #pan over medium heat. Add the
scallion whites and garlic and cook, tossing, ~{1-2%minutes}, until slightly
softened. Add the @ground pork{8%ounce} to the #pan and cook ~{3-4%minutes},
breaking the meat up into pieces, until browned and cooked through. Season
with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Return the squash and eggplant to the #pan. Add the @soy sauce{2%tablespoon}
to the #pan and cook, tossing, until the vegetables have been warmed through.

Fluff the rice with a #fork{} and serve. Plate the stir-fry on top, then squeeze
over a wedge of lime. Garnish with the scallion greens and enjoy!